video.title: DEATH NOTE
video.synopsis: When a Japanese high schooler comes into possession of a mystical notebook, he finds he has the power to kill anybody whose name he enters in it.

episodes.synopsis: Brilliant but bored high school student Light Yagami suddenly finds himself holding the power of life and death in his hands.
episodes.title: Rebirth

episodes.synopsis: While the world's criminals continue to drop dead, L meets by computer with representatives from various nations.
episodes.title: Confrontation

episodes.synopsis: Ryuk, the Shinigami, or god of death, who dropped the Death Note into the human world, warns Light that someone is on his trail.
episodes.title: Dealings

episodes.synopsis: Light--now known to the world as Kira--tests the Death Note to understand the scope of its powers by killing off six convicts in various ways...
episodes.title: Pursuit

episodes.synopsis: Soichiro Yagami demands to meet with L in person when he finds out that L has secretly brought FBI agents into Japan.
episodes.title: Tactics

episodes.synopsis: Light meets a woman at the Police Department with an urgent message for the Kira task force.
episodes.title: Unraveling

episodes.synopsis: Light uses the Death Note to try to get rid of the woman who could get him captured, and is shocked when it doesn't work.
episodes.title: Overcast

episodes.synopsis: L insists on setting up bugs and cameras in the homes of Chief Yagami and Deputy Director Kitamura...
episodes.title: Glare

episodes.synopsis: The murders continue, and L grows suspicious of Light's too-perfect behavior and decides to investigate him on his own.
episodes.title: Encounter

episodes.synopsis: L's suspicion of Light deepens, compelling him to invite Light into the investigation.
episodes.title: Doubt

episodes.synopsis: As predicted on the tapes sent to Sakura TV, news anchors and commentators who expressed doubt about Kira die one by one.
episodes.title: Assault

episodes.synopsis: With a second Kira now on the loose, L asks Light to join the task force and pose as the real Kira in order to catch the copycat.
episodes.title: Love

episodes.synopsis: Light goes to Aoyama to discover the identity of the second Kira before L becomes more suspicious.
episodes.title: Confession

episodes.synopsis: Light and Misa show each other their Death Notes, and Light asks Misa to have her shinigami Rem get rid of L.
episodes.title: Friend

episodes.synopsis: Evidence turns up that points to Misa Amane as the second Kira.
episodes.title: Wager

episodes.synopsis: Misa is in confinement, though her memories of the Death Note have been completely wiped away.
episodes.title: Decision

episodes.synopsis: After fifty days of confinement the killings continue, and Misa and Light are released.
episodes.title: Execution

episodes.synopsis: Though L is still suspicious, Light and Misa, their memories of being Kira wiped clean, return to headquarters...
episodes.title: Ally

episodes.synopsis: Matsuda, the task force member assigned to watch Misa, is eager to distinguish himself...
episodes.title: Matsuda

episodes.synopsis: L's team discovers that the Yotsuba Group meet in secret to discuss the elimination of individuals who are troublesome to their company...
episodes.title: Makeshift

episodes.synopsis: The Yotsuba Group hires Eraldo Coil to uncover L's identity.
episodes.title: Performance

episodes.synopsis: Misa succeeds in narrowing down the Kira suspects in the Yotsuba Group to one: Higuchi.
episodes.title: Guidance

episodes.synopsis: Higuchi of the Yotsuba Group attempts to kill Matsuda of the task force, and is surprised when he doesn't die after 40 seconds.
episodes.title: Frenzy

episodes.synopsis: Higuchi is captured and tells the investigators about the Death Note.
episodes.title: Revival

episodes.synopsis: Light, his memory recovered, orders Misa to begin killing after Higuchi dies.
episodes.title: Silence

episodes.synopsis: Light has removed everyone in his way and is closer to achieving his perfect world.
episodes.title: Renewal

episodes.synopsis: A new investigator steps forward--Near, a central figure in the SPK, an organization that is trying to catch Kira without relying on L.
episodes.title: Abduction

episodes.synopsis: Light, acting as L, reveals to Near that his sister Sayu has been kidnapped by someone wanting to trade her for the Death Note.
episodes.title: Impatience

episodes.synopsis: Light tries to discover where Mello and his Mafia associates are hiding and uses Misa's eyes to find the Death Note's current owner.
episodes.title: Father

episodes.synopsis: Mello busts into SPK headquarters to retrieve a photograph of himself to make sure he won't be killed by Kira.
episodes.title: Justice

episodes.synopsis: Near contacts the Japanese task force and determines that Kira is among their members.
episodes.title: Transfer

episodes.synopsis: Star newscaster Kiyomi Takada becomes Kira's spokesperson to the world...
episodes.title: Selection

episodes.synopsis: Light pretends to investigate Kiyomi...
episodes.title: Scorn

episodes.synopsis: Aizawa figures out what's going on and tells Near, who already knows about the notes.
episodes.title: Vigilance

episodes.synopsis: Light gives Kiyomi the order to finish off Near.
episodes.title: Malice

episodes.synopsis: Near, along with the SPK, meets Light and the task force at a warehouse for the final showdown.
Though Mikami has written all the investigators' names in the Death Note, a minute passes and everyone is still alive.
episodes.title: New World
